		{"id":"3507f6652eaf2429","type":"text","text":"# Wildling\n\n\n\n|              |                      |\n| ------------ | -------------------- |\n| Mance rayder | Reymás-allá-del-Muro |\n","x":3839,"y":-712,"width":472,"height":387},
		{"id":"c6994254c8a4aa4c","type":"text","text":"Prince **Rhaegar Targaryen** disappears with **Lyanna Stark**, \n\nNed Stark's sister and Robert Baratheon's betrothed. \n\nRobert and the Starks view this as a kidnapping, though later revelations suggest they eloped.","x":4200,"y":991,"width":342,"height":246},
		{"id":"1d59b019e26f7423","type":"text","text":"Brandon Stark, rides to King's Landing to demand her return.","x":4620,"y":1024,"width":250,"height":120},
		{"id":"6cc6eb999ebac13a","type":"text","text":"Not satisfied with killing the Starks, the Mad King demands the heads of both Robert Baratheon and Ned Stark. \n\nTheir mentor, **Jon Arryn**, refuses to hand them over and instead raises his banners in open revolt.","x":4653,"y":1265,"width":474,"height":182},
		{"id":"fb95b1c6a6b18b1f","type":"text","text":"The \"Mad King\" **Aerys II Targaryen** arrests him, summons their father Lord Rickard, and brutally executes them both in the throne room.","x":4960,"y":1004,"width":365,"height":160},
		{"id":"d98f96d68e831e39","type":"text","text":"La Guardia de la Noche","x":4417,"y":-678,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"7be81a3f1e0bd3e3","type":"text","text":"The Battle of the Trident\n\n\nIn single combat, **Robert caves in Rhaegar's chest** with his warhammer, winning the battle, claiming his revenge, and breaking the Targaryen army.","x":5500,"y":1053,"width":354,"height":182},
		{"id":"07d3fbf785766c03","type":"text","text":"Robert's Rebellion","x":5200,"y":1198,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"9dd5695b4dc68686","type":"text","text":"Tywin Lannister's army marches into King's Landing and sacks the city. \n\nJaime Lannister assassinates the Mad King, effectively ending the Targaryen dynasty and securing the Iron Throne for Robert.","x":5940,"y":1047,"width":429,"height":195},
		{"id":"248b9dc3a24c245b","type":"text","text":"\n\n\n| Sandor Clegane | Perro | Rostro quemado |\n| -------------- | ----- | -------------- |\n|                |       |                |\n","x":3196,"y":-325,"width":440,"height":278},
		{"id":"58c045ba2d02555f","type":"text","text":"### Targeryan\n\n\n| Rhaegar            |                                                                                                                                          |\n| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Aerys II Targaryen | rey loco                                                                                                                                 |\n| Rhaegar            | Padre Jon Nieve                                                                                                                          |\n| Viserys Targaryan  | Rey Mendigo<br>rey de los ándalos y los rhoynar y los primeros hombres, señor de los Siete Reinos y <br>Protector del Reino<br>El Dragon |\n| Daenerys Targaryen | princesa de Rocadragón<br>de la Tormenta<br>khaleesi<br>                                                                                 |\n|                    |                                                                                                                                          |\nIrri - dothrakis - enseñará a montar a caballo\nJhiqui - dothrakis - Jhiqui el idioma dothraki\nDoreah - lysena - Doreah te instruirá en las artes femeninas del amor\n\n\nHaggo -  látigo (Chicote)\nCohollo - arakh (arma dothraki)\nQotho - Arco\n","x":3758,"y":42,"width":671,"height":618},
		{"id":"e2ddb86931dfbdc7","type":"text","text":"\n| Khal Drogo |     |\n| ---------- | --- |\n|            |     |\n","x":4500,"y":55,"width":250,"height":200},
		{"id":"ed43b2c2db38bb80","type":"text","text":"Magíster Illyrio Mopatis (Ciudad Libre de Pentos)\n\nSer Willem Darry - Bravos - \n","x":4500,"y":-186,"width":408,"height":186},
		{"id":"d68c613517b8bfe0","type":"text","text":"While Robert Baratheon was securing the throne in King's Landing, \nNed Stark rode south to Dorne to finally rescue his sister.","x":6460,"y":1090,"width":560,"height":109},
		{"id":"2691f0915bd5aad7","type":"text","text":"To Ned's surprise, the tower was guarded by three of the most legendary knights of the Mad King's Kingsguard, including the formidable \n\n**Ser Arthur Dayne** (the Sword of the Morning). The fact that Rhaegar left his best knights to guard Lyanna instead of fighting at the Trident was a massive clue to her importance.","x":7080,"y":1025,"width":411,"height":240},
		{"id":"218977ef871dc100","type":"text","text":"her dying in a \"bed of blood\"—a Westerosi euphemism for severe complications during childbirth.\n\nLyanna’s true fate was that **she and Rhaegar Targaryen had eloped and conceived a child**. She was not abducted; she went willingly, though their actions plunged the realm into war.","x":7560,"y":1033,"width":491,"height":225},
		{"id":"8c9a25378008c45c","type":"text","text":"As she bled to death, Lyanna handed Ned her newborn baby boy. She knew that Robert Baratheon’s hatred for Targaryens was absolute—if Robert found out the boy was Rhaegar's son and a rival claimant to the Iron Throne, he would have the infant killed immediately.\n\nWith her dying breath, she forced her brother to make a vow, repeating the famous phrase: **\"Promise me, Ned.\"**\n\nNed kept that promise. He buried his sister, tore down the Tower of Joy to build graves for the fallen, and took the baby back to Winterfell. To protect his nephew from Robert's wrath, the rigidly honorable Ned Stark sacrificed his own reputation, claiming the boy was his own illegitimate son and naming him **Jon Snow**.","x":8160,"y":960,"width":733,"height":369}
	],
